Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags.

nug4 builds DIAGS CAUTIOUS + WERROR; under GCC 14 / C++20 (our art-stack
standard, vs upstream's C++17 default) stricter diagnostics become hard errors.
CXXFLAGS can't demote cetmodules' add_compile_options(-Werror), so drop WERROR.
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -22,7 +22,7 @@
 # -D_GLIBCXX_USE_NANOSLEEP is needed to make std::this_thread::sleep_for available. (IFDatabase)
-cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS WERROR
+cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
                        NO_UNDEFINED
                        EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic
                                    $<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX>:-D_GLIBCXX_USE_NANOSLEEP
